WHAT THE ORGANISATION DOES:
In June 2013 the charity became a member of the Together Housing Group and amended its objects as follows to reflect this new position in the North of England:1. Conservation of the natural environment  2. Urban and rural regeneration 3. Provision of Recreation and Leisure with the aim of improving conditions of life  4. Advance the life chances of young people 5. Advance education and training.

ORGANISATION CONTEXT:
Wharf Street, BLACKBURN, BB1 1JD, Greater Manchester, Greater Manchester. ~70 staff; income on record £8,578,267.

RECOMMENDED VAxAI ENTRY: Workflow review + selective VA

WHY ADMIN / AI PRESSURE IS HIGH:
Housing and homelessness services create tenancy, referral and contract-reporting administration. Children and family services span casework, safeguarding, referrals and programme reporting.

CHARITY / SECTOR AI CONTEXT (use in conversation):
Many housing charities use housing management systems but still rely on spreadsheets and email for referrals, contract evidence, and partner reporting. AI for drafting support notes or summarising case updates is early-stage; staff often need training before tool adoption.

WHERE VA ALONE IS NOT THE RIGHT LEAD:
VA alone is weak for real-time homelessness triage or statutory housing applications — automate referral logging and reporting templates first.

STRONGEST REASON TO CONTACT:
NEWGROUND TOGETHER shows housing & homelessness delivery with material admin load — Map referral-to-tenancy handoffs without replacing your HMS

HOW TO PRESENT VAxAI:
Position VAxAI as wraparound support: review existing systems, train staff on practical AI, and offer flexible virtual assistance for follow-through — not a CRM or case-system replacement.

SUGGESTED CALL HOOKS / DISCOVERY QUESTIONS:
• Map referral-to-tenancy handoffs without replacing your HMS
• Train staff on safe AI drafting for support notes with human review
• Reduce contract reporting prep with structured templates and VA follow-up

DISCOVERY PROMPTS FOR THIS CALL:
• Which reporting, referral, or volunteer workflows consume the most coordinator time?
• What systems are in use today — and where do spreadsheets or email still carry the load?
• Has anyone been asked to explore AI, and is there a policy or governance concern?
• What would success look like in 90 days for the operations or programmes team?

