WHAT THE ORGANISATION DOES:
Our objectives: To relieve poverty and promote health and development in the Bongo District of the Upper East Region of Ghana and other rural areas of Ghana, by means including the provision of improved sanitation, water supply and education.We are currently building about 20 latrines each year in a rural village.

ORGANISATION CONTEXT:
Hadleigh, Suffolk, Suffolk. ~8 staff; income on record £240,000.

RECOMMENDED VAxAI ENTRY: Training + policy guidance

WHY ADMIN / AI PRESSURE IS HIGH:
Community centre delivering activities for older people and carers needs booking, transport and volunteer admin.

CHARITY / SECTOR AI CONTEXT (use in conversation):
Health charities must balance efficiency with clinical governance. AI training and workflow review around non-clinical admin (scheduling, reporting drafts) is usually the safest entry point.

WHERE VA ALONE IS NOT THE RIGHT LEAD:
Do not propose AI for clinical decisions or patient triage — focus on administrative coordination and governed drafting support.

STRONGEST REASON TO CONTACT:
Hadleigh Community Resource Centre shows health & wellbeing delivery with material admin load — Identify admin tasks that can be AI-assisted without clinical risk

HOW TO PRESENT VAxAI:
Position VAxAI as wraparound support: review existing systems, train staff on practical AI, and offer flexible virtual assistance for follow-through — not a CRM or case-system replacement.

SUGGESTED CALL HOOKS / DISCOVERY QUESTIONS:
• Identify admin tasks that can be AI-assisted without clinical risk
• Develop practical AI guidance for helpline and coordination teams
• Review appointment and referral workflows across partners

DISCOVERY PROMPTS FOR THIS CALL:
• Which reporting, referral, or volunteer workflows consume the most coordinator time?
• What systems are in use today — and where do spreadsheets or email still carry the load?
• Has anyone been asked to explore AI, and is there a policy or governance concern?
• What would success look like in 90 days for the operations or programmes team?

